---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="answer_architecture_question — ArchLens"
  description="Answer stable Java maintenance questions with evidence, unresolved facts, and ambiguity preserved."
>
  <section class="tool-page">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="tool-page-header">
        <h1 class="tool-page-title">answer_architecture_question</h1>
        <span class="tool-page-badge">Query</span>
      </div>

      <p class="tool-page-intro">
        A question-oriented view over the indexed graph. It combines the relevant graph nodes and
        edges into four stable contracts: persistence destination, consumer context, grouped
        change impact, and transaction context. Missing runtime configuration is returned as an
        unresolved fact instead of being guessed.
      </p>

      <h2 class="tool-section-label">Arguments</h2>
      <table class="arg-table">
        <thead><tr><th>Name</th><th>Type</th><th>Required</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>family</td><td>string</td><td>yes</td><td><code>persistence_destination</code>, <code>consumer_context</code>, <code>impact</code>, or <code>transaction_context</code>.</td></tr>
          <tr><td>entrypoint</td><td>string</td><td>by family</td><td>Entrypoint ID, name, or <code>METHOD /path</code>.</td></tr>
          <tr><td>component</td><td>string</td><td>by family</td><td>Component simple name or qualified ID.</td></tr>
          <tr><td>query</td><td>string</td><td>—</td><td>Persistence operation, entity, or component query.</td></tr>
          <tr><td>param / method</td><td>string</td><td>—</td><td>Optional parameter or method selector.</td></tr>
          <tr><td>maxDepth</td><td>integer</td><td>—</td><td>Impact depth. Default: <code>4</code>.</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>

      <h2 class="tool-section-label">Example</h2>
      <div class="terminal-card">
        <div class="terminal-top"><span></span><span></span><span></span><strong>tools/call</strong></div>
        <pre><code>{`{
  "name": "answer_architecture_question",
  "arguments": {
    "family": "persistence_destination",
    "entrypoint": "POST /api/orders/{id}",
    "param": "id"
  }
}`}</code></pre>
      </div>

      <h2 class="tool-section-label">Output</h2>
      <p class="tool-page-intro">
        Every response contains <code>family</code>, <code>status</code>,
        <code>subject</code>, <code>answer</code>, <code>unresolved</code>, and
        <code>ambiguous</code>. A <code>partial</code> or <code>ambiguous</code> status is a valid,
        evidence-bearing answer. Family-specific sections include evidence chains, destinations,
        upstream/downstream context, grouped impact, or transaction scope transitions.
      </p>

      <h2 class="tool-section-label">Related tools</h2>
      <div class="related-pills">
        <a href="/tools/index-workspace" class="related-pill">index_workspace</a>
        <a href="/tools/query-architecture-graph" class="related-pill">query_architecture_graph</a>
        <a href="/tools/trace-data-flow" class="related-pill">trace_data_flow</a>
        <a href="/tools/render-pipeline" class="related-pill">render_pipeline</a>
      </div>

      <a href="/#tools" class="tool-back-link">← All tools</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
